window.EQ_DATA["AMZN"] = {"ticker": "AMZN", "meta": {"ticker": "AMZN", "nome_empresa": "Amazon.com, Inc.", "setor": "eCommerce / Cloud / AI Infrastructure / Advertising", "geografia": "US", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~2100", "fiscal_year_end": "31 de dezembro", "tags": ["setor/ecommerce", "setor/cloud", "setor/ai-infra", "setor/digital-ads", "geografia/us", "moat/escala", "moat/logistics", "moat/ecossistema", "status/em_estudo"], "status_tese": "em_estudo", "data_criacao": "2026-04-21", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-05-27"}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>AMZN — Amazon.com, Inc.</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>One-liner</strong>: #1 eCommerce ocidental + #1 cloud (AWS) + #3 digital ads + emerging player AI infra (Trainium ASIC, Anthropic partnership). Maior <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler</a> por CapEx absoluto ($147B TTM Q1 FY26, +67% YoY). <strong>AWS aceleração estrutural validada Q1 FY26: +28% YoY, fastest em 15 quarters</strong>. Custom silicon (Graviton + Trainium + Nitro) atingiu <strong>$20B+ revenue run rate internal</strong> (Jassy: <strong>$50B se standalone</strong>, &quot;<strong>top 3 data center chip business in the world</strong>&quot;). Compromissos forward atualizados (Q1 FY26 call): <strong>&gt;$225B em revenue commitments para Trainium</strong> (Anthropic + OpenAI + Uber + outros). <strong>Backlog AWS Q1 = $364B</strong> (não inclui Anthropic deal $100B+ → pro-forma &gt;$465B = ~3 anos de receita AWS). Meta committed to <strong>&quot;tens of millions of Graviton cores&quot;</strong> — cross-validation Meta↔AWS no CPU layer. <strong>🆕 10-Q (filed 2026-05-05) revela equity commitments em labs líderes: Anthropic $74B balance-sheet + $30B post-quarter forward (facility) + OpenAI $50B Series C ($15B done + $35B committed) = ~$154B locked-in.</strong></blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>Três big businesses</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>North America/International retail (combined ~65% revenue)</strong>: marketplace 1P + 3P + subscriptions (Prime). Margens baixas historicamente; expansion trajectory em curso.</li><li><strong>AWS (~17% revenue, ~40% EBIT)</strong>: maior cloud do mundo. 30%+ market share public cloud. Crescimento 18% FY24, acelerando FY25.</li><li><strong>Advertising (~9% revenue)</strong>: sponsored products em Amazon.com + Prime Video ads + Twitch + DSP. High margin. Canal #3 digital ads globais.</li></ol>\n<h3>AWS — o crown jewel</h3>\n<ul><li>FY24 revenue: $107.6B</li><li>EBIT: ~$40B (37% margin)</li><li>Key products: EC2, S3, Lambda, Bedrock (Anthropic Claude + outros)</li><li><strong>Trainium/Inferentia</strong>: ASICs próprios via Annapurna Labs (acquired 2015). Roda Anthropic training/inference.</li><li><strong>Anthropic</strong>: ~$8B investment total. Principal cliente GenAI AWS. Commitment: Anthropic roda Claude primarily on AWS Trainium.</li></ul>\n<h3>🆕 AWS margin inflection 1Q26 — Bedrock mix + Anthropic deal economics</h3>\n<p>Fonte: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">SemiAnalysis 27-May-2026</a> (Eliahou Ontiveros, Brookhart, Huang, Patel) — usando Tokenomics 2.0 Model + Datacenter Industry Model.</p>\n<p><strong>Quadro de mix AI por hyperscaler em 1Q26:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>CSP</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">AI % de total revenue</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">TaaS % de AI revenue</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">IaaS % de AI revenue</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>AWS</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>10%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>37% (Bedrock)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~63%</td></tr><tr><td>Azure</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">27%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">&lt;20% (Foundry pequeno)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>80%+</strong></td></tr><tr><td>GCP</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">36%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~20% (Gemini API)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>80%+</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ AWS tem <strong>o menor AI mix</strong> mas o <strong>maior TaaS share dentro do AI mix</strong>. TaaS dá margem materialmente maior que IaaS wholesale → AWS captura mais $ de lucro por $ de receita AI.</p>\n<p><strong>Bedrock dynamics 1Q24 → 1Q26:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Bedrock como % AWS AI revenue: <strong>9% (1Q25) → 37% (1Q26)</strong>.</li><li>Bedrock Q/Q growth: <strong>+170% em 1Q26</strong>; +60% em 4Q25 (AMZN earnings calls).</li><li>Bedrock run-rate ~<strong>US$5,5B</strong>; vasta maioria (80-90%+) dos clientes usando Anthropic.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Estrutura econômica do deal Bedrock/Anthropic (SemiAnalysis entendimento):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>(i) Flat IaaS fee + (ii) revenue share + (iii) performance hurdles acima de níveis de spend/throughput.</li><li>Termos públicos no Bedrock: produto é <strong>vendido pela Anthropic</strong> (&quot;Anthropic terms govern use&quot;), cliente é <strong>faturado pela AWS</strong> (&quot;Deployed on AWS&quot;).</li><li>Resultado contábil: <strong>Anthropic books full revenue</strong> dos tokens. <strong>AWS recebe infrastructure fee + distribution/revenue share</strong> — é a revenue share que infla margem.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Sensibilidade ilustrativa (Tokenomics):</strong> assumindo 25% AWS/Anthropic revenue share + $7.5M/MW Bedrock IaaS fee + $6.5M/MW AMZN opex, com Anthropic gross revenue de $25M/MW → <strong>AWS EBIT margin ~53%</strong>, $30M/MW → ~57%.</p>\n<p><strong>Cálculo 1Q26</strong>: Anthropic Bedrock revenue ~<strong>US$26M/MW</strong> → Bedrock EBIT margin implícita <strong>~55%</strong>. <strong>Bedrock respondeu por ~30% do step-up Y/Y em Gross Profit Dollars apesar de ser 4% da receita total AWS.</strong> Margem incremental AWS 1Q26 reportada (+213bp Q/Q) é <strong>primariamente Bedrock</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Para 2Q26</strong>: SemiAnalysis vê Anthropic ARR/MW ~<strong>US$42M</strong>, mix Bedrock → <strong>53% do AWS AI revenue</strong>, contribuição <strong>+9pp</strong> ao growth total da AWS. Nota técnica: como Anthropic ARR é gross-basis, <strong>Bedrock isolado é levemente diluitivo no GM blended</strong> vs current ~low-60% inference GM Anthropic — mas é fortemente accretive em EBIT margin AWS.</p>\n<p><strong>Quote citável</strong> — Matt Garman (AWS CEO, Nov-2025):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;Our AWS Trainium chips, designed in-house for AI workloads, now power more than 50% of Amazon Bedrock token usage.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>Implicação dupla: (1) Trainium ramp tem demand pull natural via Bedrock — chip caseiro encaixa porque hardware é abstraído do cliente em TaaS. (2) ~50% do uso de Bedrock = ~50% de US$5,5B run-rate = ~<strong>US$2,5-3B de tokens rodando em Trainium</strong> (input para upside roadmap T3/T4).</p>\n<p><strong>Anthropic 1Q26 — backdrop que sustenta o mix shift:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>ARR US$30B (+US$21B net new no quarter); SemiAnalysis projeta &gt;US$100B fim de 2026.</li><li>Inference GM: <strong>-94% (2024) → 38% (2025) → mid-60s (1Q26)</strong>.</li><li>WSJ 20-May-2026: Anthropic deve ser <strong>Operating Income positivo em 2Q26</strong> (ex-SBC).</li><li>API revenue Anthropic +<strong>~13x YoY</strong> (driver direto Bedrock).</li><li>Anthropic skewa enterprise/API (vs OpenAI skewa consumer + custos de free inference).</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Capacity advantage</strong> (SemiAnalysis Datacenter Model):</p>\n<ul><li>AWS adiciona mais MW que qualquer rival em <strong>2025, 2026 e 2027</strong>.</li><li>Power procurement antecipado (PPAs com Talen, Vistra, NiSource).</li><li>Novo design de DC com modularidade/prefab acelerando build pace.</li><li>Construção próxima a 2GW em Indiana + Mississippi a &quot;lighting speed&quot;.</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações para a tese FOX</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Margin trajectory upgrade</strong>: a aceleração validada em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> tem agora um <strong>driver granular de margem</strong> (Bedrock mix + revenue share Anthropic) que sustenta o re-rating.</li><li><strong>Trainium offtake validado em produção</strong>: &gt;50% do uso Bedrock significa que Trainium não é só &quot;potential&quot; — está rodando workload Anthropic em escala.</li><li><strong>Risco residual</strong>: revenue share da AMZN no deal Anthropic é função de pricing decisions da Anthropic. Se Anthropic baixar token prices pra ganhar share vs OpenAI, AWS take cai proporcionalmente.</li><li><strong>Cross-vendor leverage</strong>: AMZN agora vende <strong>OpenAI tokens</strong> via Bedrock (além de Claude). MSFT ganhou Claude em Foundry. Os 3 hyperscalers (AMZN/MSFT/GOOGL) são os únicos com acesso aos 3 frontier models — todos os outros (ORCL, neoclouds) ficam fora desse anel.</li></ul>\n<h3>Retail business transformation</h3>\n<ul><li>&quot;Year of Efficiency&quot; 2023 (similar ao Meta): layoffs 27k+, fulfillment reorganização.</li><li>Jassy (CEO since 2021) tornou retail profitability-first. Margins expansion 2023-24.</li><li>Prime: 200M+ global members.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management</h2><ul><li><strong>CEO</strong>: Andy Jassy (desde Jul/2021, succedeu Jeff Bezos). Ex-head of AWS.</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: Brian Olsavsky.</li><li><strong>Chairman</strong>: Jeff Bezos — saiu do CEO 2021, continua chairman e driver estratégico.</li><li><strong>AWS CEO</strong>: Adam Selipsky → Matt Garman (desde Jun/2024).</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros</h2><p>Os dados do recap Paulo (2024-recap) estão na tabela acima. <strong>[ ] Números FY25 específicos a verificar</strong> — 10-K FY25 (filed Feb/2026) <strong>não está no vault</strong> (apenas hash-named PDFs em <code>F:/Gestao/Research/Internacional/Amazon/AMZN fillings/</code> que precisariam identificação como fizemos na NVDA).</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 — primeiro reality check pós-FY25 (29-Apr-2026)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-04-30</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-press-release\">press release oficial 8-K EX99.1</a>. Relatório PDF Fox: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-30-AMZN-1Q26.pdf\" title=\"outputs/AMZN/1Q26/2026-04-30-AMZN-1Q26.pdf\">2026-04-30-AMZN-1Q26.pdf</a> (nota <strong>9/10</strong>).</p>\n<h3>Headline metrics Q1 FY26</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Q1 FY25</th><th>Q1 FY26</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Net sales</td><td>$155,7B</td><td><strong>$181,5B</strong></td><td><strong>+17%</strong> (+15% ex-FX)</td></tr><tr><td>AWS revenue</td><td>$29,3B</td><td><strong>$37,6B</strong></td><td><strong>+28%</strong> ← 15-quarter high</td></tr><tr><td>Operating income</td><td>$18,4B</td><td><strong>$23,9B</strong></td><td><strong>+30%</strong>, margin 13,1% (recorde)</td></tr><tr><td>AWS OI</td><td>$11,5B</td><td>$14,2B</td><td>+23%, margin 37,7% (-178 bps YoY)</td></tr><tr><td>Net income GAAP</td><td>$17,1B</td><td>$30,3B</td><td>+77% (inclui $16,8B Anthropic mark-up)</td></tr><tr><td>EPS diluted</td><td>$1,59</td><td>$2,78</td><td>+75%</td></tr><tr><td>OCF TTM</td><td>$113,9B</td><td>$148,5B</td><td><strong>+30%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>CapEx Q1</strong></td><td>$25,0B</td><td><strong>$44,2B</strong></td><td><strong>+77%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>FCF TTM</strong></td><td>$25,9B</td><td><strong>$1,2B</strong></td><td><strong>-95%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Long-term debt</td><td>—</td><td><strong>$119,1B</strong></td><td>+$53B QoQ (bond offering massivo)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>AWS aceleração — confirmação estrutural</h3>\n<p>Trajetória YoY % (do release supplemental):</p>\n<ul><li>Q4 24: +19%</li><li>Q1 25: +17%</li><li>Q2 25: +17%</li><li>Q3 25: +20%</li><li>Q4 25: +24%</li><li><strong>Q1 26: +28%</strong> ← fastest em 15 quarters</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Run rate AWS atingiu $150B</strong>. Custom silicon (Graviton + Trainium + Nitro) chegou a <strong>$20B+ revenue run rate</strong>, growing triple-digit YoY.</p>\n<h3>AI infrastructure announcements Q1 FY26 (validam tese)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>OpenAI commitment: ~2GW de Trainium capacity</strong> via AWS pra modelos frontier — ramp começa 2027</li><li><strong>Anthropic: até 5GW</strong> das gerações atuais e futuras de Trainium</li><li><strong>2,1M+ AI chips landed</strong> nos últimos 12 meses (&gt;50% Trainium)</li><li><strong>1M+ Nvidia GPUs</strong> a deployer começando 2026</li><li><strong>Cerebras</strong> collaboration via Bedrock — único cloud com fastest AI inference em LLMs</li><li>Bedrock processou mais tokens em Q1 do que todos os anos anteriores combinados; <strong>customer spend +170% QoQ</strong></li><li><strong>AWS Agent Registry, Bedrock AgentCore, Claude Mythos Preview, Claude Opus 4.7</strong> lançados/anunciados</li></ul>\n<h3>Q2 FY26 guidance</h3>\n<ul><li>Revenue: <strong>$194-199B</strong> (+16% a +19% YoY) — beat de 3-5% vs consenso $189B</li><li>Op Income: <strong>$20-24B</strong> (mid $22B vs $19,2B Q2 25, +15% YoY)</li><li>Prime Day em Q2 nos US (em 2025 foi Q3) → puxa receita pra cá</li><li>FX headwind ~10 bps</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações para tese</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>AWS reacceleration</strong>: validado e acelerando além do que LG modelava. Q1 26 +28% vs LG FY26E 21% YoY → AWS rodando 7pp acima do LG implícito. ✓ <strong>Trainium economics</strong>: Anthropic 5GW + OpenAI 2GW = ~7GW de commitments forward. Demand pull, não push. ✓ <strong>Margin expansion</strong>: 13,1% consolidated margin é recorde histórico, +132 bps YoY. ✓ <strong>Advertising</strong>: $17,2B trimestral, $70B+ TTM run rate (Jassy disclosed). +24% YoY. ⚠️ <strong>CapEx ramp</strong>: $44B trimestral / $147B TTM (+67%) — magnitude acima do LG implícito. P&amp;E líquido +$40B em UM trimestre. ⚠️ <strong>FCF TTM colapsou pra $1,2B</strong> (-95% YoY) — primeiro tri perto de zero desde COVID. ⚠️ <strong>Long-term debt +$53B QoQ</strong> — bond offering Mar/2026 ($37-42B reportado) confirmado no balance sheet. Net debt/EBITDA de 0,26x → 0,47x.</p>\n<p><strong>Position update</strong>: convicção sobe. Capex/FCF é o swing factor — se H2-26 confirmar AWS &gt;35% YoY, abre espaço para revisar FY27 LG para cima ($236B AWS / $79B AWS EBIT). Asymmetric upside ainda favorável dada a opcionalidade Trainium standalone + grocery TAM + Leo + Zoox.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 10-Q — disclosures novas vs press release/call (filed 2026-05-05)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-05</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">10-Q SEC accession 0001018724-26-000014, 54 páginas, OCR&amp;#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime</a>. Foco: itens <strong>não cobertos</strong> no press release nem no earnings call já ingeridos.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 OpenAI — equity commitment de $50B (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;In Q1 2026, we invested <strong>$15.0 billion in Series C Preferred Stock of OpenAI</strong>, and we also entered into an equity commitment letter agreement (the &#x27;Letter Agreement&#x27;), pursuant to which we agreed to purchase additional shares of Series C Preferred Stock (the &#x27;Commitment Shares&#x27;) with an aggregate purchase price of <strong>$35.0 billion</strong> (the &#x27;Commitment Amount&#x27;).&quot;</em> — 10-Q Note 2 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-12\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-12\">p.12</a>)</blockquote>\n<ul><li><strong>$15B já investido</strong> Q1 26 + <strong>$35B comprometido</strong> = <strong>$50B total</strong> em OpenAI equity</li><li><strong>Triggers</strong> para chamar o $35B: (i) OpenAI atingir milestones específicas, OU (ii) OpenAI fazer Public Listing Transaction (IPO/direct listing)</li><li><strong>Hard deadline</strong>: se não investido até <strong>2028-12-31</strong>, Letter Agreement expira</li><li>Acompanha <strong>commercial arrangement</strong> (AWS cloud + AWS chips para OpenAI) + <strong>joint collaboration</strong> (modelos OpenAI rodando em AWS — o GPT-5.4 em Bedrock mencionado no call já é fruto disso)</li><li><strong>Nada disso foi quantificado no press release nem no call do dia 29-Apr</strong> — apenas o &quot;GPT-5.4 live em Bedrock&quot; foi sinalizado. O equity commitment de $50B é disclosure exclusivo do 10-Q.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Implicação</strong>: AMZN agora detém posição estratégica em <strong>ambos</strong> os labs líderes (Anthropic + OpenAI). Posição combinada já desembolsada ou comprometida em equity &gt; <strong>$100B</strong> (ver Anthropic abaixo).</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Anthropic — exposição balance-sheet $74B + post-quarter $30B+ (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<p>Quadro completo de exposição AMZN→Anthropic ao final de Q1 FY26 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-11\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-11\">p.11-12</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Componente</th><th>Dec 31, 2025</th><th>March 31, 2026</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Convertible notes (AFS, fair value)</td><td>$45.8B</td><td><strong>$42.2B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Nonvoting preferred stock (carrying value)</td><td>$14.8B</td><td><strong>$32.0B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total exposição AMZN→Anthropic</strong></td><td><strong>$60.6B</strong></td><td><strong>$74.2B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>AOCI unrealized gain (notes)</td><td>n/a</td><td>$36.3B</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Subsequent events (após March 31, 2026)</strong> — não estavam disponíveis no press release nem no earnings call:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>+$5.0B investidos em Anthropic nonvoting preferred stock</strong></li><li><strong>NEW $20.0B financing facility</strong>: AMZN disponibiliza facility a Anthropic, expira 30 meses após liquidity event. Drawable conforme Anthropic atinge milestones de delivery de compute capacity. Draws em forma de <strong>convertible notes</strong> (ou common stock pós-IPO).</li><li><strong>Option</strong> para investir até <strong>$5.0B adicionais</strong> em rondas futuras de equity Anthropic (se exercido, reduz facility disponível na mesma magnitude)</li><li><strong>Amended commercial arrangement</strong> com <strong>contractual obligations relacionadas à performance de AWS chips</strong> (i.e., AMZN se compromete formalmente a entregar performance de Trainium para Anthropic)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Compromisso forward total Anthropic</strong>: até <strong>+$30B</strong> em capital novo (5+20+5).</p>\n<p><strong>Implicação</strong>: contraste com narrativa &quot;$8B cumulative investment&quot; mencionada anteriormente — o capital efetivamente comprometido é uma ordem de magnitude maior. O <strong>financing facility é estrutura nova</strong> (não convertível tradicional) e amarra o capital ao cumprimento de milestones de compute pela AMZN. <strong>Cross-link</strong>: o &quot;ramping&quot; do Trainium é literalmente o trigger pro pagamento do facility.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Globalstar — definitive merger agreement signed 2026-04-13 (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<p>Earnings call do dia 29-Apr mencionou &quot;Globalstar acquisition planejado&quot;. O 10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-15\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-15\">p.15</a>) confirma que o <strong>definitive agreement foi assinado em 13-Apr-2026</strong> com termos:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Consideração</strong>: $90.00 por ação em cash OU 0.3210 ações AMZN (capped a $90 valor)</li><li><strong>Cash election cap</strong>: máximo 40% das ações Globalstar em cash (proration mecanism)</li><li><strong>Downward adjustment</strong>: até <strong>$110M</strong> se Globalstar não atingir certos operational milestones de satellite replacement</li><li><strong>Closing esperado em 2027</strong>, sujeito a regulatory approvals</li><li>AMZN adquire também a <strong>equity stake da Apple</strong> num Globalstar SPV (parte do deal Apple-Globalstar legacy)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Long-term debt — março 2026 issuance: $53.8B total (vs $37-42B reportado)</strong></h3>\n<p>Detalhe completo do bond offering (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-17\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-17\">p.17</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Tranche</th><th>Tamanho</th><th>Maturidades</th><th>Stated Rate</th><th>Effective Rate</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>March 2026 USD Notes</strong></td><td><strong>$37.0B</strong></td><td>2028-2076</td><td>3.85%-6.05%</td><td>3.97%-6.12%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>March 2026 Euro Notes</strong></td><td><strong>€14.5B (~$16.8B)</strong></td><td>2028-2064</td><td>2.50%-4.85%</td><td>2.59%-4.88%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>TOTAL March 2026</strong></td><td><strong>~$53.8B</strong></td><td>mix</td><td>mix</td><td>mix</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul><li>Combined weighted-average remaining life Notes: <strong>14.2 years</strong></li><li>Euro tranche designada como <strong>net investment hedge</strong> (mitigação de FX da translation de operações foreign)</li><li>Total face value de long-term debt: $68.8B → <strong>$122.6B</strong> (+$53.8B QoQ)</li><li>Total fair value Notes: $61.1B → <strong>$113.6B</strong></li><li><strong>No financial covenants</strong> sob qualquer um dos Notes</li><li>Aggregate <strong>revolving credit unused</strong>: $20.0B ($15B Credit Agreement até Nov 2028 + $5B 364-day facility até Out 2026); $9.4B em letters of credit não utilizados</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>PP&amp;E por segmento — AWS é 76% dos net adds Q1 (NOVO detalhe)</strong></h3>\n<p>Net additions to property and equipment Q1 FY26 (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-24\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-24\">p.24</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>PP&amp;E Dec 31, 2025</th><th>PP&amp;E March 31, 2026</th><th>Q1 net adds</th><th>% of total</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>North America</td><td>$122.0B</td><td>$129.2B</td><td>$11.1B</td><td>20%</td></tr><tr><td>International</td><td>$30.6B</td><td>$30.9B</td><td>$1.7B</td><td>3%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>AWS</strong></td><td><strong>$190.1B</strong></td><td><strong>$223.1B</strong></td><td><strong>$41.5B</strong></td><td><strong>76%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Corporate</td><td>$14.3B</td><td>$14.3B</td><td>$0.4B</td><td>1%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Consolidated</strong></td><td><strong>$357.0B</strong></td><td><strong>$397.5B</strong></td><td><strong>$54.8B</strong></td><td>100%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Inclui <strong>$1.3B de PP&amp;E adicionado em finance leases</strong> dentro do AWS Q1 FY26 (vs $0 no Q1 FY25). Indica uso crescente de leasing pra capacidade DC.</p>\n<p>D&amp;A AWS Q1 FY26: <strong>$7.3B</strong> (+66% YoY) — confirma que o capex está chegando em P&amp;L via depreciação rapidamente, comprimindo margem AWS curto-prazo.</p>\n<h3><strong>Tax — discrete items Anthropic-driven + IRS Notice 2026-7 (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<ul><li>Tax provision Q1 FY26: <strong>$9.6B</strong> (24% effective rate, up de 21% Q1 FY25)</li><li>Inclui <strong>$4.1B de net discrete tax expense</strong> primarily attribuível aos net gains de Anthropic ($16.8B mark-up no other income)</li><li><strong>IRS Notice 2026-7 (publicado 2026-02-18)</strong> trouxe guidance sobre tratamento de previously capitalized R&amp;D costs — <strong>expected to result in significant decrease of 2024 and 2025 cash taxes paid</strong> (aplicado retroativamente)</li><li>Cash paid for income taxes Q1 FY26: $1.3B (vs $0.9B Q1 FY25)</li><li>Tax contingencies: $6.6B → $6.7B</li><li>Disputas tax abertas materiais: <strong>Luxembourg Tax Authority</strong> (basis de intangíveis distribuídos para US em 2021), <strong>Indian Tax Authority</strong> (cloud services fees pagos AMZN US)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>Energy contracts — derivative disclosure: 200M MWh, 15-yr WAL (NOVO detalhe)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-8\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-8\">p.8</a>) detalha que AMZN tem contratos de electricity supply para operações sob derivative accounting:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>~200 milhões de megawatt-horas</strong> comprometidos</li><li><strong>Weighted-average remaining duration: ~15 anos</strong></li><li>Maioria das MWh entregues além dos próximos 9 anos</li><li>Alguns contratos exempt sob NPNS (normal purchases / normal sales) ou aguardando regulatory approval</li><li>Exposição relevante a power constraints de DCs — locked-in supply de longo prazo</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>AWS backlog — duração 5.5 yr (NOVO detalhe)</strong></h3>\n<p>Earnings call deu o número $364B. 10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-9\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-9\">p.9</a>) adiciona:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Weighted-average remaining life dos long-term contracts: 5.5 anos</strong></li><li>$364B ÷ 5.5 anos = <strong>~$66B/ano de revenue contratada de AWS</strong> (run-rate-equivalent monetização do backlog)</li><li>Comparado ao run rate atual AWS de <strong>$150B/ano</strong> = backlog cobre ~44% do run rate ao longo de 5.5 anos (não inclui novos contratos firmados ao longo do tempo)</li><li>Adicional: <strong>expansion do existing $38B OpenAI commitment</strong> explicitada — este $38B já era prior, foi expandido em Q1 26 (magnitude da expansão truncada no OCR mas confirmada no balance dos numbers)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Trajetória do backlog AWS (recuperado via re-OCR do 10-K FY25 página 51):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Período</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Backlog</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">WAL</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">$/ano contratado</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Q4 FY25 (31-Dec-2025)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$244B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4.1 anos</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$59B/ano</td></tr><tr><td>Q1 FY26 (31-Mar-2026)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$364B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.5 anos</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$66B/ano</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Δ QoQ</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$120B (+49%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+1.4 anos</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$7B/ano</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Salto QoQ massivo é <strong>deal-driven</strong> (OpenAI $38B+ expandido, Anthropic compute, Meta Graviton, Uber, NVIDIA, U.S. Army etc.) — backlog crescendo mais rápido que receita reportada (+49% QoQ vs AWS revenue +28% YoY) sinaliza <strong>demand pull contratada</strong> acima da trajetória usage-driven atual.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 GCP backlog ULTRAPASSOU AWS pela 1ª vez — Q1 FY26</strong></h3>\n<p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-07</strong> após <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-press-release\">GOOGL Q1 FY26 press release</a> (29-Apr-2026): Sundar Pichai disclosed <strong>GCP backlog &quot;nearly doubling QoQ to over $460 billion&quot;</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>🆕 Atualizado 2026-05-07 com 10-Q</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">GOOGL Q1 FY26 10-Q</a>) — número exato e methodology change:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;As of March 31, 2026, we had <strong>$467.6 billion of remaining performance obligations (&#x27;revenue backlog&#x27;), of which $462.3 billion related to Google Cloud</strong>.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Methodology change</strong>: GOOGL &quot;elected to change our reporting of revenue backlog to now also include contracts with an original expected term of one year or less&quot; em Q1 26. Comparação com Q4 25 ($240B) <strong>não é apples-to-apples</strong> — parte do salto QoQ é adoção de novo escopo de medida.</p>\n<p><strong>Cross-comparison atualizada (números corretos pós-10-Q):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">AWS Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>GCP Q1 FY26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Comentário</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Revenue Q1 (YoY)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$37.6B (+28%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$20.0B (<strong>+63%</strong>)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP cresce 2.25x mais rápido</td></tr><tr><td>Run rate ($/ano)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$150B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$80B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">AWS ainda 1.9x maior em absoluto</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Backlog (apples-to-apples)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$364B</strong> (&gt;1yr WAL 5.5y)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$462.3B</strong> (Cloud) ou <strong>$467.6B</strong> (Alphabet total)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP &gt; AWS, mas methodology GOOGL agora inclui contratos curtos (Q4 25 $240B = só &gt;1yr)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Backlog comparable basis (&gt;1yr only)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$364B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>&lt;$462.3B</strong> (não disclosed)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">Gap real é menor</td></tr><tr><td>Backlog/run rate</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.4x</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~5.75x (Cloud)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP visibility maior</td></tr><tr><td>Backlog QoQ</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$120B (+49%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$220B (+92%)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">Mas GCP delta inflado por methodology change</td></tr><tr><td>Cloud op margin</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">37.7%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">32.9%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">AWS lead 5pp em base maior</td></tr><tr><td>YoY trajectory</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+24%→+28% (3Q)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+48%→+63% (5Q acelerando)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP 5 quarters seguidos acelerando</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Implicação para tese AMZN</strong>:</p>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Sinal de alerta competitivo claro</strong>: pela primeira vez no ciclo, GCP supera AWS em demand contratada forward. AWS ainda é #1 em revenue absoluto, mas:</p>\n<ul><li>Se trajetória de aceleração GCP continuar 2-3 trimestres, <strong>gap de growth fechará rápido</strong> ($460B backlog GCP × 5.75x rotation vs AWS $364B × 2.4x → GCP run rate convergindo)</li><li>O caso &quot;AWS é o hyperscaler #1, ponto&quot; precisa ser <strong>re-litigated</strong> com este data point</li><li>GCP tem <strong>stack próprio</strong> (TPU + Gemini + DeepMind + Search infra ROIC) que entrega margin 32.9% — paridade estrutural com AWS conquistada</li></ul>\n<p>⚠️ <strong>Mas também tem leitura positiva pra AMZN</strong>:</p>\n<ul><li>O <strong>mercado total</strong> (cloud + AI infra) está crescendo tão rápido que <strong>ambos</strong> podem capturar muito sem competir zero-soma</li><li>AMZN tem <strong>diversification superior</strong> (retail + ads + AWS) — não depende só de Cloud</li><li>AMZN custom silicon (Trainium + Graviton + Nitro) = <strong>$50B run rate standalone equivalent</strong> (Jassy Q1 26 call) já é &quot;top 3 chip business in the world&quot; — competitivo com TPU stack do Google</li></ul>\n<p>✓ <strong>Não invalida a tese AMZN</strong>, mas <strong>sobe a régua de execução</strong>: AWS precisa <strong>re-acelerar para +30%+</strong> nos próximos 2-3 trimestres pra defender a narrativa de &quot;hyperscaler #1 inquestionável&quot;. Q2 FY26 print (final julho) vira catalisador crítico.</p>\n<p>Cross-references:</p>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> — seção &quot;Q1 FY26 — primeiro reality check&quot; detalha o backlog GCP $460B + Cloud margin 32.9%</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — comparison atualizada no concept page</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>Buyback — pausado pelo segundo Q consecutivo (continuidade)</strong></h3>\n<ul><li>$6.1B remaining no programa $10B autorizado em Mar/2022</li><li><strong>Zero recompras em Q1 FY26</strong> (também zero em Q1 FY25)</li><li>Capital allocation está 100% direcionado pra: CapEx + equity stakes (Anthropic + OpenAI) + Globalstar acquisition pendente</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>Forward commitments table — $569B total (NOVO contexto)</strong></h3>\n<p>Tabela completa de contractual commitments (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-15\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-15\">p.15</a>) at March 31, 2026:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Bucket</th><th>2026 (9mo)</th><th>2027</th><th>2028</th><th>2029</th><th>2030</th><th>Thereafter</th><th><strong>Total</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Long-term debt P&amp;I</td><td>$5.9B</td><td>$13.6B</td><td>$16.7B</td><td>$11.1B</td><td>$10.7B</td><td>$145.6B</td><td><strong>$203.5B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Operating lease liabilities</td><td>$11.7B</td><td>$13.9B</td><td>$12.9B</td><td>$11.6B</td><td>$10.4B</td><td>$49.6B</td><td><strong>$110.1B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Finance lease liabilities</td><td>$1.5B</td><td>$1.7B</td><td>$1.8B</td><td>$1.4B</td><td>$1.2B</td><td>$8.8B</td><td><strong>$16.5B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Financing obligations</td><td>$0.4B</td><td>$0.6B</td><td>$0.6B</td><td>$0.6B</td><td>$0.7B</td><td>$7.2B</td><td><strong>$10.2B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Leases not yet commenced</strong></td><td>$5.1B</td><td>$9.6B</td><td>$7.2B</td><td>$7.3B</td><td>$7.3B</td><td>$69.8B</td><td><strong>$106.3B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Unconditional purchase obligations</td><td>$19.1B</td><td>$15.8B</td><td>$8.5B</td><td>$7.3B</td><td>$7.3B</td><td>$45.7B</td><td><strong>$103.8B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Other commitments</td><td>$2.6B</td><td>$1.8B</td><td>$1.2B</td><td>$1.0B</td><td>$1.0B</td><td>$11.3B</td><td><strong>$18.8B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td><strong>$46.5B</strong></td><td><strong>$57.1B</strong></td><td><strong>$48.9B</strong></td><td><strong>$40.4B</strong></td><td><strong>$38.6B</strong></td><td><strong>$337.9B</strong></td><td><strong>$569.3B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Notar: <strong>$106B em leases not yet commenced</strong> (futuras DCs/fulfillment) + <strong>$104B unconditional purchase obligations</strong> (energy + content + property + software) = <strong>$210B em commitments forward que ainda não estão no balance sheet</strong>.</p>\n<h3><strong>Risk factors — semicondutor concentration + memory chips (sharpened)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q Item 1A risk factors atualiza (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-43\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-43\">p.43</a>):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;we rely on a <strong>limited group of suppliers for semiconductor products, including products related to artificial intelligence infrastructure such as graphics processing units</strong>. Constraints on the availability of these products could adversely affect our ability to develop and operate artificial intelligence technologies, products, or services.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>Forward-looking statement reconhece explicitamente &quot;<strong>resource and supply volatility, including for memory chips</strong>&quot; como risk factor. Conecta com narrativa de Andy no call sobre memory cost spike + cloud migration tailwind.</p>\n<h3>Implicações para tese (10-Q delta)</h3>\n<ul><li>✓ <strong>Strategic equity positioning é mais profundo do que aparente</strong>: $74B Anthropic + $50B OpenAI + post-quarter $30B Anthropic = <strong>$154B em equity commitments</strong> em labs líderes. Locks in commercial relationships estruturalmente.</li><li>✓ <strong>AWS é 76% do net CapEx Q1</strong>: confirma que a expansão de PP&amp;E é AI-infra, não fulfillment. Margin pressure curto-prazo (D&amp;A AWS +66% YoY) é expected.</li><li>⚠️ <strong>Bond offering $53.8B (vs $37-42B falado)</strong>: balance sheet leverage subiu mais do que o sinal antes do filing. Net debt/EBITDA de 0.26x → <strong>0.47x</strong> (ainda baixo, mas trajetória).</li><li>⚠️ <strong>Tax discrete $4.1B em Q1 26</strong>: effective rate Q1 = 24% (up de 21% Q1 25). FY26 effective rate normalizado a observar — mgmt estimou &quot;adversely affected by state income taxes, favorably impacted by U.S. federal R&amp;D credit&quot;.</li><li>✓ <strong>Long-term debt WAL 14.2 anos</strong>: AMZN está locking in cost of capital por longo prazo. Combina com strategy de CapEx 10-yr cycle.</li><li>✓ <strong>Globalstar deal definitivo signed</strong>: removed da categoria &quot;planejado&quot; para &quot;binding&quot;. Apple legacy stake bought-out. Closing 2027.</li></ul>\n<h3>Cross-links propagados</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — AMZN agora também é major equity backer de OpenAI ($50B), além de Anthropic ($74B + $30B forward). Ambos os principais consumidores frontier estão <strong>financeiramente acoplados</strong> ao stack AWS+Trainium.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=META\" title=\"wiki/META\">META</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">MSFT</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> — comparar magnitude de equity stakes em AI labs: AMZN + Anthropic + OpenAI = ~$154B comprometido, vs MSFT-OpenAI relationship structure (~$13B inicial + entitlements).</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — $106B leases not yet commenced + $54.8B Q1 net adds = pipeline de CapEx forward maior do que o run-rate atual.</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto</h2><ul><li>[x] ~~1 PDF status NEEDS_OCR~~ — AWS-Anthropic-scaling OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li>[x] ~~AWS FY25 full-year revenue e EBIT atualizados~~ — via FY25 10-K: AWS $128,7bn (+20%), OP $45,6bn</li><li>[x] ~~Anthropic stake — valuation implícita e termos~~ — 10-Q FY26-Q1 detalha: $42.2B convertibles + $32.0B prefs = $74.2B exposição balance-sheet; post-quarter +$5B prefs + $20B financing facility + $5B option (ver seção 10-Q)</li><li>[x] ~~Trainium v2/v3 roadmap~~ — earnings call FY26 Q1 deu: T2 sold out / T3 shipping start 2026 30-40% melhor / T4 18mo away já reservado</li><li>[ ] <strong>AMZN fillings</strong> folder em F:\\ tem PDFs hash-named (similar a NVDA original). Identificar e renomear em Fase 2.</li><li>[ ] Trainium volumes específicos (units, capacity em GW deployed) — call deu commits forward mas não capacity instalada</li><li>[ ] Kuiper CapEx e revenue timeline — converter PDF específico (backlog).</li><li>[ ] Ads breakdown por subsegmento (sponsored products, DSP, Prime Video, Twitch).</li><li>[ ] OpenAI Series C — preço de entrada implícito vs valuation atual OpenAI (~$500B reportado). $15B em Series C pode estar em valuation diferente.</li><li>[ ] Geographic revenue split (US vs International) — 10-Q dá só por segmento (NA/Intl/AWS), não por geografia detalhada de AWS revenue.</li><li>[ ] Rodar Perguntas 1-4 para AMZN usando base histórica agora disponível.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-05-27</strong>: ✅ <strong>SemiAnalysis &quot;Anthropic Growth and Bedrock Mix Drive AWS Margins Higher While Peers Lag&quot; ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic</a> — Eliahou Ontiveros/Brookhart/Huang/Patel). Cross-company com âncora AMZN. Adicionados: novo trigger (margin inflection via Bedrock mix + Anthropic deal), nova subseção &quot;AWS margin inflection 1Q26&quot; em &quot;AWS — o crown jewel&quot; com economia do deal Bedrock detalhada. <strong>Datapoints centrais</strong>: (1) AWS margin <strong>+213bp Q/Q em 1Q26</strong> vs MSFT IC negativo e GCP flat; (2) Bedrock como % AWS AI revenue <strong>9% (1Q25) → 37% (1Q26)</strong>, Q/Q growth <strong>+170%</strong>, run-rate ~<strong>US$5,5B</strong>, 80-90% usando Anthropic; (3) AI como % AWS revenue <strong>2% (1Q24) → 10% (1Q26)</strong> — AWS tem menor AI mix mas mix interno TaaS-heavy é margin accretive; (4) <strong>Trainium &gt;50% dos tokens Bedrock</strong> (Matt Garman Nov-2025 disclose) → ~US$2,5-3B de tokens rodando em silicon caseiro; (5) Anthropic 1Q26 <strong>US$30B ARR (+US$21B net new)</strong>, inference GM <strong>-94% (2024) → 38% (2025) → mid-60s (1Q26)</strong>, Op Income <strong>positivo em 2Q26 ex-SBC</strong> (WSJ 20-May), API rev <strong>+~13x YoY</strong>, projeção SemiAnalysis <strong>&gt;US$100B ARR YE2026</strong>; (6) Estrutura deal Bedrock/Anthropic: flat IaaS fee + revenue share + performance hurdles; Anthropic books revenue gross (Anthropic é seller), AWS captura IaaS fee + distribution fee/revenue share → <strong>Bedrock EBIT margin implícita ~55% em 1Q26</strong> com US$26M/MW; (7) <strong>Bedrock responde por ~30% do step-up Y/Y em Gross Profit Dollars apesar de 4% da revenue total</strong>; (8) AWS lidera capacity adds 2025/26/27 — power procurement antecipado, novo DC design modular. <strong>Implicação central</strong>: o +213bp margin Q/Q tem <strong>driver granular</strong> que sustenta o re-rating; Trainium offtake validado em produção; risco residual é pricing decision da Anthropic. Cross-links propagados: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">MSFT</a> (datacenter pause + OpenAI absorbing capacity), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> (EBTIT margin com DeepMind em Alphabet-Level Activities), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> (IP vendor TPU-Anthropic royalty), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a> (TaaS economics), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (AWS lidera MW adds).</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: wiki criada a partir da Fase 1 (8 PDFs — 3 Paulo internal recaps + Trainium + AWS 2Q25 preview + BofA bull/bear + all-hyperscalers CapEx + Anthropic scaling NEEDS_OCR). Não incluídos os hash-named da AMZN fillings (identification pendente).</li><li><strong>2026-04-23</strong>: AWS-Anthropic-scaling.md destravado via rapidocr-onnxruntime (status NEEDS_OCR removido).</li><li><strong>2026-04-24</strong>: <strong>Fase 2 ingestão</strong> — 5 10-Ks históricos FY21/FY22/FY23/FY24/FY25 convertidos via OCR. Adicionada seção &quot;Evolução histórica FY20 → FY25&quot; com tabelas de net sales + operating income + EPS por ano. Insights novos: (a) AWS aceleração clara de +13% FY23 → +20% FY25; (b) International virou positiva em FY24; (c) NA OP turnaround de −$2,8bn → +$29,6bn em 3 anos (maior swing empresarial do ciclo); (d) FY25 charges one-off $5,2bn (FTC settlement + severance) — adj EBIT ~$85bn, margin 11,9%.</li><li><strong>2026-05-07</strong> (later): 🔄 <strong>Refinamento cross-link GOOGL via 10-Q</strong>: (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> ingested) — números corrigidos: backlog GOOGL <strong>total $467.6B</strong> (vs Cloud-only $462.3B). <strong>Methodology change importante</strong>: GOOGL &quot;elected to change our reporting of revenue backlog to now also include contracts with an original expected term of one year or less&quot; em Q1 26 — comparação com Q4 25 ($240B) <strong>não é apples-to-apples</strong>. Implicação: gap real Cloud GCP vs AWS é menor do que sugerido (GOOGL comparable basis &gt;1yr only seria &lt;$462.3B; AWS continua $364B em base 5.5y WAL). Adicional GOOGL findings cross-relevantes para AMZN: (a) <strong>Anthropic $40B deal formalizado pelo GOOGL</strong> ($10B + $30B equity derivative milestones-contingent) → <strong>GOOGL forward em Anthropic pode ser maior que AMZN forward</strong> ($30B AMZN facility + $5B option + $5B prefs); (b) <strong>GOOGL vendendo TPU externamente</strong> = paralelo direto ao AMZN sinalizar venda de Trainium racks — convergência de business model nos hyperscalers; (c) <strong>Wiz closing $29.5B + Intersect $5.9B</strong> = GOOGL fez $35B M&amp;A num quarter (vs AMZN ~$15B). Mantém recomendação anterior <strong>TRIM marginal AMZN para 9-10%</strong> mas com nuance: a comparação Cloud-vs-Cloud é menos extrema do que parecia no press release; tese AWS &quot;execução sólida com GCP fechando gap&quot; continua válida — só a magnitude fica menor.</li><li><strong>2026-05-07</strong>: ⚠️ <strong>Cross-link GOOGL Q1 FY26</strong>: GCP backlog $460B <strong>ultrapassou AWS $364B pela 1ª vez no ciclo</strong>. Adicionada subseção &quot;GCP backlog ULTRAPASSOU AWS&quot; com comparison detalhada. Implicação: AWS ainda é #1 em revenue absoluto ($150B run rate vs GCP ~$80B) mas em <strong>demand contratada forward</strong> GCP virou líder. Se trajetória continuar 2-3Q (GCP +63% YoY accelerating, AWS +28%), narrativa de &quot;hyperscaler #1 inquestionável&quot; precisa ser re-litigated. Não invalida tese AMZN (diversification + custom silicon + retail/ads), mas sobe régua: <strong>Q2 FY26 print (final julho) vira catalisador crítico</strong> — AWS precisa re-acelerar para +30%+ pra defender posição.</li><li><strong>2026-05-05</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 10-Q ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — SEC accession 0001018724-26-000014, 54 páginas, OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime — PDF era image-based, sem camada de texto). Adicionada seção &quot;Q1 FY26 10-Q — disclosures novas vs press release/call&quot;. <strong>Disclosures NÃO cobertos no press release nem no earnings call</strong>: (1) <strong>OpenAI equity commitment $50B total</strong> ($15B já investido em Series C Preferred + $35B Letter Agreement, deadline 2028-12-31 ou Public Listing); (2) <strong>Anthropic exposure $74.2B em balance sheet</strong> ($42.2B convertibles AFS + $32.0B nonvoting prefs); (3) <strong>Anthropic post-quarter actions: +$5B prefs + $20B financing facility (drawable em milestones de compute capacity) + $5B option</strong> = até $30B forward incremental; (4) <strong>Globalstar definitive agreement signed 2026-04-13</strong> ($90/share cash ou 0.3210 AMZN, 40% cap cash, $110M downward adjustment, close 2027); (5) <strong>March 2026 bond issuance $53.8B total</strong> (USD $37B + EUR €14.5B/$16.8B) — vs $37-42B falado anteriormente; (6) <strong>PP&amp;E AWS = 76% dos net adds Q1</strong> ($41.5B de $54.8B), D&amp;A AWS +66% YoY explica margin pressure; (7) <strong>Tax discrete items $4.1B Q1 atribuível a Anthropic gains</strong> + <strong>IRS Notice 2026-7 (Feb/2026)</strong> trouxe relief retroativo em R&amp;D capitalization; (8) <strong>Energy contracts derivative</strong>: 200M MWh comprometidos com 15-yr WAL para electricity supply de DCs; (9) <strong>AWS backlog WAL 5.5 anos</strong> (10-Q dá duração; press release só o $364B); (10) <strong>OpenAI commercial expansion</strong>: existing $38B commitment foi expandido (magnitude truncada no OCR); (11) <strong>Buyback continuou pausado</strong> (zero recompras Q1 26 e Q1 25, $6.1B remaining no programa $10B); (12) <strong>Forward commitments table $569B total</strong> com $106B em leases not yet commenced + $104B em unconditional purchase obligations; (13) Risk factors <strong>explicitamente</strong> mencionam &quot;limited group of suppliers for semiconductors including GPUs&quot; + &quot;memory chips supply volatility&quot; — conecta com narrative de Andy. Cross-links propagados pra <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (AMZN agora equity backer dos dois labs líderes), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=META\" title=\"wiki/META\">META</a>/<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">MSFT</a>/<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=GOOGL\" title=\"wiki/GOOGL\">GOOGL</a> (comparar magnitude equity stakes), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (pipeline forward maior que run-rate). <strong>Implicação central</strong>: AMZN tem ~$154B em equity commitments comprometidos em AI labs, locking in commercial relationships estruturalmente — escala muito maior que reportada anteriormente.</li><li><strong>2026-05-05</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 earnings call ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — Bloomberg Final Transcript, 15 páginas, call do dia 29-Apr-2026). Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q1 FY26 earnings call — adições materiais&quot;. <strong>Disclosures novos não cobertos no press release</strong>: (1) <strong>Trainium revenue commitments $225B+</strong> (vs ~$112B implícito antes — material upward revision); (2) <strong>Custom silicon $50B run rate se standalone — top 3 data center chip business</strong> (Andy explicit); (3) Trainium roadmap: T2 ~30% better vs GPUs / T3 +30-40% vs T2 / T4 já reservada; (4) <strong>Trainium economics quantificados: tens of $bn CapEx savings/yr + several 100 bps margin advantage</strong>; (5) <strong>Meta committed to &quot;tens of millions of Graviton cores&quot;</strong> — cross-validation Meta↔AWS no CPU layer; (6) <strong>Backlog AWS $364B (ex-Anthropic deal $100B+)</strong> = pro-forma &gt;$465B; (7) <strong>AWS AI = 260x larger em 3-yr mark</strong> vs original AWS ($15B vs $58M); (8) <strong>NVDA partnership reaffirmed</strong> (&quot;as long as I can foresee&quot; — não é replacement); (9) <strong>OpenAI GPT-5.4 live em Bedrock + 5.5 coming + Bedrock Managed Agents (Stateful Runtime Environment)</strong> preview lançado; (10) <strong>Apple direct-to-device deal via Leo</strong> confirmado + <strong>Globalstar acquisition planejado</strong>; (11) <strong>Internal AI productivity case study: 5 AI-forward people em 65 dias = 40-50 people em 1 ano</strong> (~40-60x effort reduction); (12) <strong>Memory shortage = tailwind escondido pra cloud migration</strong> (suppliers prioritize cloud providers); (13) <strong>Sell Trainium racks &quot;good chance over next couple of years&quot;</strong> — vetor novo standalone post-2026; (14) Andy: &quot;<strong>plan is largely the same</strong>&quot; em CapEx (vs Meta que raised same day) — framework intacto; (15) Cash CapEx Q1 = <strong>$43.2B</strong> (vs press release $44.2B incl finance leases). Wiki cross-links propagados pra <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=META\" title=\"wiki/META\">META</a> (Graviton), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> (Trainium incremental wins), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> ($50B run rate).</li><li><strong>2026-04-30</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 press release ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-press-release\">FY26-Q1-press-release</a> — 8-K EX99.1, 14 páginas). Primeiro relatório trimestral via skill <code>atualizacao-trimestral</code> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-30-AMZN-1Q26.pdf\" title=\"outputs/AMZN/1Q26/2026-04-30-AMZN-1Q26.pdf\">PDF Fox 18 páginas</a>, nota <strong>9/10</strong>). <strong>Updates materiais</strong>: (1) Revenue Q1 <strong>$181,5B (+17% YoY, +15% ex-FX)</strong> — beat consensus $177B; (2) <strong>AWS +28% YoY = fastest em 15 quarters</strong>; (3) <strong>Custom silicon $20B+ run rate</strong> triple-digit growth; (4) <strong>OpenAI 2GW Trainium + Anthropic 5GW</strong> = ~7GW commitments forward; (5) <strong>2,1M+ AI chips landed</strong> em 12 meses (&gt;50% Trainium); (6) Op margin consolidada <strong>13,1% — recorde histórico</strong>; (7) AWS margin <strong>37,7% (-178 bps YoY)</strong> — capex depreciation pesando; (8) <strong>CapEx Q1 $44B (+77% YoY) / TTM $147B (+67%)</strong> — P&amp;E +$40B QoQ; (9) <strong>FCF TTM colapsou pra $1,2B (-95% YoY)</strong>; (10) <strong>Long-term debt $119B (+$53B QoQ)</strong> — bond offering Mar/2026 ($37-42B) confirmado; (11) Q2 FY26 guide <strong>$194-199B</strong> above consensus; (12) Advertising TTM <strong>&gt;$70B</strong>; (13) Stores units +15% (highest desde post-COVID); (14) Net Income +77% inclui $16,8B Anthropic mark-up (ex-Anthropic EPS ~-1% YoY); (15) Amazon Leo (Delta, Vodafone, Globalstar acquisition planejado), Zoox (Uber agreement), Project Hail Mary $615M box office. Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q1 FY26 — primeiro reality check pós-FY25&quot;. Posição update: <strong>convicção sobe</strong>, FY26 LG pode precisar revisar para cima se AWS continuar a &gt;35%.</li><li><strong>2026-05-20</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">NVDA Q1 FY27 earnings call, 20-May-2026</a> (Colette). <strong>AWS = top tier NVDA customer com escala inédita</strong>: <em>&quot;Starting this year, AWS will add <strong>more than 1 million Blackwell and Rubin GPUs</strong> and are collaborating on Spectrum networking.&quot;</em> Datapoints: (1) <strong>&gt;1M Blackwell+Rubin GPUs</strong> = compromisso de mais de 12 meses de capacity NVDA, paralelo ao roadmap Trainium ($225B commitments, T3/T4 sold out) — confirma &quot;ASIC + GPU, não vs&quot; em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>; (2) <strong>Spectrum networking collab</strong> = AWS adotando Spectrum X (Ethernet AI), não só InfiniBand — vetor de share NVDA networking ($15bn ~3x YoY); (3) Anthropic deal NVDA-AWS: NVDA suporta capacity Anthropic via AWS/Azure/CoreWeave/Space xAI — confirma Anthropic-AWS deepening (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> já tinha $74.2B exposure). Implicação: AWS está <strong>expandindo capacity NVDA aceleradamente</strong> mesmo com Trainium escalando — não substituição, é <strong>adição estrutural</strong>. Cross-link: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (CapEx materializando) + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera-Rubin</a> (early customer).</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault</h2><h3>SEC Filings (10-Ks) — <em>ingested 2026-04-24</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a> — ano pandemia (535 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a> — ano do stress (260 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> — início do turnaround (299 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> — margin expansion clara (280 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — <strong>mais recente</strong> — AWS aceleração +20%, $5,2bn charges one-off (273 KB)</li></ul>\n<h3>Earnings calls + press releases</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — <strong>10-Q Q1 FY26</strong> SEC accession 0001018724-26-000014 (54 páginas, OCR&#x27;d 2026-05-05) — period ended 2026-03-31</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-press-release\">FY26-Q1-press-release</a> — 8-K EX99.1 Q1 FY26 (14 páginas)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">FY26-Q1-earnings-call</a> — Bloomberg Final Transcript Q1 FY26 (15 páginas, call 29-Apr-2026)</li></ul>\n<h3>Documentos internos do Paulo</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2021-06-original-case\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2021-06-original-case\">2021-06-original-case</a> — tese original Jun/2021</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2024-recap\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2024-recap\">2024-recap</a> — <strong>recap 2024</strong> (framework Pergunta 1-4, números atualizados)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZ-New\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/AMZ-New\">AMZ-New</a> — AMZ New (análise subsequente)</li></ul>\n<h3>Research</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Trainium-scaling-AI\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/Trainium-scaling-AI\">Trainium-scaling-AI</a> — Trainium economics</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AWS-Anthropic-scaling\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/AWS-Anthropic-scaling\">AWS-Anthropic-scaling</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-AWS-2Q-preview\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2025-AWS-2Q-preview\">2025-AWS-2Q-preview</a> — AWS 2Q25 preview</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear\">2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear</a> — bull/bear debate</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2024-11-CapEx-all-hyperscalers\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2024-11-CapEx-all-hyperscalers\">2024-11-CapEx-all-hyperscalers</a> — CapEx comparativo all hyperscalers</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic</a> — SemiAnalysis 27-May-2026: AWS margin inflection +213bp Q/Q via Bedrock mix + Anthropic deal economics; Trainium &gt;50% tokens Bedrock; Anthropic blowout Q1 (US$30B ARR, mid-60s inference GM)</li></ul>\n<h3>Backlog (em F:\\, priorizar em Fase 2)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>AMZN fillings folder (hash-named 10-Ks/10-Qs/proxies)</strong> — identificar e renomear (padrão NVDA)</li><li>Amazon Kuiper, Amazon Sizing China Problem, Alexa is Losing Billions</li><li>2025 Global eCommerce Handbook, BofA Bull/Bear debates, Clouded Judgement</li><li>Sell Side subfolder (Citi, CS, GS, MS) — cada banco tem seus researches</li><li>Cloud Study AMZ, Cloud estudo, Jefferies Te</li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (resumo — framework Paulo 2024 recap)</h2><p><strong>Segmentos 2024 (do recap Paulo):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>2023 ($M)</th><th>2024 ($M)</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Retail Products (1P)</td><td>231,872</td><td>247,029</td><td>+6.5%</td></tr><tr><td>Physical Stores</td><td>20,030</td><td>21,215</td><td>+5.9%</td></tr><tr><td>Retail Products (3P)</td><td>140,053</td><td>156,146</td><td>+11.5%</td></tr><tr><td>Subscription</td><td>40,209</td><td>44,374</td><td>+10.4%</td></tr><tr><td>Ads</td><td>46,906</td><td>56,214</td><td>+19.8%</td></tr><tr><td>AWS</td><td>90,757</td><td>107,556</td><td>+18.5%</td></tr><tr><td>Other</td><td>4,958</td><td>5,425</td><td>+9.4%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Net Revenue</strong></td><td><strong>574,785</strong></td><td><strong>637,959</strong></td><td><strong>+11.0%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Key financials FY24:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Revenue: <strong>$638B</strong> (+11% YoY)</li><li>Gross margin: 48.9% (FY24, +187 bps)</li><li><strong>EBIT margin: 10.8%</strong> (FY24, <strong>+434 bps</strong> — major margin expansion)</li><li>Net income: $59.2B (+94.7% YoY)</li><li>FCF net of SBC: $38.2B</li><li>CapEx: $116B (+36% YoY — maior entre hyperscalers em valor absoluto)</li><li>AWS EBIT: ~$40B (~37% margin em AWS stand-alone)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>10-year track record (2014-2024):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Revenue CAGR: 21.8% (de $89B a $638B)</li><li>EBIT margin: 0.2% (2014) → 10.8% (2024) — transformação de &quot;low-margin e-commerce&quot; pra &quot;high-margin cloud + ads platform&quot;</li><li>Share count aumentando ligeiramente (vs GOOGL/MSFT que reduziram)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Fox 2025E (do recap):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Revenue total: $702B (+10% YoY)</li><li>EBIT: $85.7B (12.2% margin)</li><li>AWS: $130B (+21% YoY)</li><li>AWS EBIT: $45.5B (35% margin)</li><li>Net Income: $70B (+27% YoY)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Triggers:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>AWS reacceleration</strong> — research <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-AWS-2Q-preview\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2025-AWS-2Q-preview\">2025-AWS-2Q-preview</a> &quot;Following Azure&#x27;s acceleration playbook&quot;</li><li><strong>Anthropic partnership</strong> — $8B cumulative investment. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AWS-Anthropic-scaling\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/AWS-Anthropic-scaling\">AWS-Anthropic-scaling</a> (NEEDS_OCR). Anthropic &quot;home&quot; é AWS, roda em Trainium.</li><li><strong>Trainium/Inferentia ASIC ramp</strong> — ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>. Cost advantage estrutural vs NVDA GPUs.</li><li><strong>🆕 AWS margin inflection via Bedrock mix + economia do deal Anthropic</strong> (SemiAnalysis 27-May-2026): margem operacional AWS <strong>+213bp Q/Q em 1Q26</strong> enquanto MSFT IC caiu e GCP estagnou. Driver = mix shift de IaaS → TaaS (Bedrock 9% → 37% do AWS AI revenue em 4 trimestres) e a revenue share fee do deal Anthropic. <strong>Bedrock respondeu por ~30% do step-up YoY em Gross Profit Dollars com só 4% da receita.</strong> Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic</a> + <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a> seção TaaS economics.</li><li><strong>🆕 Trainium powering &gt;50% do uso de tokens no Bedrock</strong> (Matt Garman, AWS CEO, Nov-2025 — disclosed pelo CEO; sinal forte de TCO competitivo no inferência/RL). Cross-link <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</li><li><strong>Ads business</strong>: $56B FY24 (+20% YoY) — mercado subestima. Margins muito maiores que retail.</li><li><strong>Retail margin expansion</strong>: retail EBIT margin era negativa 2022; 2024 positivo. Jassy &quot;cost-to-serve&quot; optimization.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Riscos:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx ocular</strong>: $116B FY24 → projetando $150B+ FY25/FY26 (Fox). Se AI demand desacelerar, hit em FCF.</li><li><strong>Amazon Kuiper</strong>: bet $20B+ em satellite internet pra competir com Starlink. Unclear ROI. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Amazon_Kuiper.pdf\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/Amazon_Kuiper.pdf\">Amazon_Kuiper.pdf</a> em backlog.</li><li><strong>Alexa</strong>: WSJ reportou prejuízo bilionário histórico; Rufus-era AI pode virar Alexa monetizável mas resultado incerto.</li><li><strong>China/tariffs</strong>: exposure indireto (sellers chineses em 3P marketplace). Research <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Amazon Sizing the China Problem\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/Amazon Sizing the China Problem\">Amazon Sizing the China Problem</a> em backlog.</li></ul></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation</h2><ul><li><strong>[ ] Pergunta 4 pendente.</strong></li><li>Research <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear\">2025-04-BofA-Bull-Bear</a> cobre bull/bear debate.</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/AMZN.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Evolução histórica — retrospectiva FY20 → FY25</h2><p>Adicionada <strong>2026-04-24</strong> via ingestão de 5 10-Ks SEC FY21-FY25 (OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime). Fontes: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a>.</p>\n<h3>Net Sales por Segmento ($M, calendar year)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>North America</th><th>International</th><th>AWS</th><th><strong>Consolidated</strong></th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY20</td><td>236.282</td><td>104.412</td><td>45.370</td><td><strong>386.064</strong></td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>FY21</td><td>279.833</td><td>127.787</td><td>62.202</td><td><strong>469.822</strong></td><td><strong>+22%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY22</td><td>315.880</td><td>118.007</td><td>80.096</td><td><strong>513.983</strong></td><td><strong>+9%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY23</td><td>352.828</td><td>131.200</td><td>90.757</td><td><strong>574.785</strong></td><td><strong>+12%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>387.497</td><td>142.906</td><td>107.556</td><td><strong>637.959</strong></td><td><strong>+11%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td><strong>426.305</strong></td><td><strong>161.894</strong></td><td><strong>128.725</strong></td><td><strong>716.924</strong></td><td><strong>+12%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Operating Income por Segmento ($M) — a recuperação épica</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>North America</th><th>International</th><th>AWS</th><th><strong>Consolidated</strong></th><th>Consol margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY22</td><td><strong>(2.847)</strong></td><td><strong>(7.746)</strong></td><td>22.841</td><td><strong>12.248</strong></td><td>2,4%</td></tr><tr><td>FY23</td><td>14.877</td><td>(2.656)</td><td>24.631</td><td><strong>36.852</strong></td><td>6,4%</td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>24.967</td><td>3.792</td><td>39.834</td><td><strong>68.593</strong></td><td>10,8%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td><strong>29.619</strong></td><td><strong>4.750</strong></td><td><strong>45.606</strong></td><td><strong>79.975</strong></td><td><strong>11,2%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>EPS diluted</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>EPS diluted</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY21</td><td>$3,24</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>FY22</td><td><strong>$(0,27)</strong></td><td><strong>loss</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY23</td><td>$2,90</td><td>recovery</td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>$5,53</td><td>+91%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td><strong>$7,17</strong></td><td><strong>+30%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Análise da trajetória</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>FY20 → FY21 (pandemia boom)</strong>: +22% consolidated. Revenue saltou de $386B para $470B. AWS +37%. Over-expansão da capacidade.</li><li><strong>FY22 (ano do stress)</strong>: crescimento freou para +9%. <strong>International OP loss de −$7,7bn</strong>. NA também negativa. Só AWS sustentou. <strong>EPS negativo ($−0,27)</strong>. Rivian writedown pesou. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a></li><li><strong>FY23 (Jassy turnaround)</strong>: &quot;Cost-to-serve&quot; optimization de Jassy vira o volante. NA volta para $14,9bn OP. Consolidated OP triplica para $36,9bn. <strong>Gross margin expansion começa</strong>. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a></li><li><strong>FY24 (margin expansion clara)</strong>: OP $68,6bn (+86% YoY). NA OP $25bn (+68%). International positiva. AWS +62% OP. <strong>EBIT margin 10,8% vs 6,4% FY23 — +440bps em um ano</strong>. EPS $5,53. <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a></li><li><strong>FY25 (expansão sustentada, charges não recorrentes)</strong>: OP $80bn (+17%) <strong>apesar de $5,2bn de charges one-off</strong> ($2,5bn FTC settlement Q3 + $2,7bn severance — role eliminations). <strong>EBIT ex-charges ~$85bn = 11,9% margin</strong>. AWS +20% revenue (aceleração!) e +14% OP para $45,6bn. EPS $7,17 (+30%). <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a></li></ol>\n<h3>Principais descobertas (via 10-Ks históricos)</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>AWS aceleração FY25 é real e mensurável</strong>: de +13% FY23 → +19% FY24 → <strong>+20% FY25</strong>. AWS OP $45,6bn (+14%) — margem ~35% sustentada em alta base. Consistente com research &quot;AWS reacceleration&quot; no vault.</li><li><strong>International finalmente virou positiva em FY24</strong> (+$3,8bn) após 3 anos de prejuízos operacionais. FY25 $4,75bn. Estrutura agora sustentável.</li><li><strong>NA segment OP expansão dramática</strong>: $(2,8)bn em FY22 → $29,6bn em FY25. <strong>&gt;$32bn de swing em 3 anos</strong> — maior turnaround empresarial do ciclo. Impulsionado por (a) aumento de ads sales, (b) 3P marketplace mix, (c) cost-to-serve efficiency, (d) regional fulfillment (reduziu shipping cost per unit).</li><li><strong>Charges FTC + severance FY25 são one-offs conhecidos</strong>: $2,5bn FTC settlement Q3 2025 + $2,7bn severance (role eliminations). <strong>Adj EBIT FY25 normalizado ~$85bn, margin ~11,9%</strong>.</li><li><strong>Leverage</strong>: Long-term debt reduzido de $58,3bn (FY23) para $52,6bn (FY24). Long-term lease liabilities $77,3bn → $78,3bn. <strong>Balance sheet fortalecendo mesmo com CapEx recorde</strong>.</li><li><strong>Interest income relevante</strong>: $4,7bn FY24 vs $2,9bn FY23 — balance de caixa rendendo em rates altos. Estrutura &quot;bank-like&quot; do balance sheet.</li></ol>\n<h3>Mix evolution (% of net sales, FY20 → FY25)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY20</th><th>FY25</th><th>ΔShare</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>AWS</td><td>11,8%</td><td><strong>18,0%</strong></td><td>+6,2pp</td></tr><tr><td>International</td><td>27,0%</td><td>22,6%</td><td>-4,4pp</td></tr><tr><td>NA</td><td>61,2%</td><td>59,5%</td><td>-1,7pp</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>AWS shift para ~18% do mix com margem ~35% = explica a maior parte da margin expansion consolidada.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 earnings call — adições materiais (29-Apr-2026)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-05</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/FY26-Q1-earnings-call\">Bloomberg Final Transcript (15 páginas)</a>. Disclosures novos não cobertos no press release:</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Trainium revenue commitments $225B+</strong> (vs ~$112B implícito antes)</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;For our custom AI silicon, we&#x27;ve recently shared very large, multi-year, multi-gigawatt Trainium commitments from the <strong>two leading AI labs in the world, in Anthropic and OpenAI</strong>, as well as an increasing number of companies like <strong>Uber</strong> betting on Trainium. And we now have <strong>over $225 billion in revenue commitments for Trainium</strong>.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Material upward revision do número anterior. Esses $225B se acumulam com <strong>backlog AWS de $364B (ex-Anthropic deal $100B+)</strong> = pro-forma backlog <strong>&gt;$465B</strong>, cobrindo <strong>&gt;3 anos</strong> do run rate AWS atual ($150B).</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Custom silicon = $50B run rate se standalone — top 3 data center chip business</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;If our chips business was a standalone business and sold chips produced this year to AWS and other third parties, as other leading chip companies do, our annual revenue run rate would be <strong>$50 billion</strong>. As best as we can tell, our custom silicon business is now <strong>one of the top three data center chip businesses in the world</strong>. The speed at which we&#x27;ve gotten here is extraordinary.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Implicação: AMZN custom silicon (Graviton + Trainium + Nitro) já está no patamar <strong>NVDA + Broadcom semi-custom</strong>. Quase certamente top 3 atrás de NVDA e AVGO. <strong>Sell Trainium racks externally</strong> sinalizado: <em>&quot;Good chance we&#x27;re going to sell racks over the next couple of years&quot;</em> — vetor novo standalone post-2026.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Trainium roadmap explícito — pricing power escalonado</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Chip</th><th>Status Q1 FY26</th><th>Price-performance vs comparable GPUs</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Trainium2</strong></td><td>&quot;Largely sold out&quot;</td><td><strong>~30% better</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Trainium3</strong></td><td>Started shipping start of 2026</td><td><strong>30-40% more vs T2</strong> = ~50-60% better than GPUs</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Trainium4</strong></td><td>~18 meses from broad availability</td><td>&quot;Already reserved&quot;</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul><li>Bedrock <strong>runs most of its inference on Trainium</strong></li><li><strong>80% of Fortune 100</strong> using Bedrock; <strong>125,000+ customers</strong> total</li><li>Bedrock <strong>customer spend +170% QoQ</strong>; processou <strong>mais tokens em Q1 do que em todos os anos anteriores combinados</strong></li><li>Trainium2 <strong>token throughput +4x em 2025</strong> (efficiency gain converte direto em mais capacity entregue)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Trainium economics quantificados</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;At scale, we expect Trainium will save us <strong>tens of billions of dollars of CapEx each year</strong> and provide <strong>several 100 basis points of operating margin advantage</strong> versus relying on others&#x27; chips for inference.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Validação quantitativa da tese de moat de custom silicon. Material — primeira vez Andy cota &quot;$10s of bn savings/ano&quot; + &quot;100s bps margin advantage.&quot; Reforça o framework de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Meta commitment: &quot;tens of millions of Graviton cores&quot;</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We also just announced that <strong>Meta is committed to using tens of millions of Graviton cores</strong>. Graviton is our industry-leading CPU chip, which allows Meta to run the <strong>CPU-intensive workloads behind agentic AI</strong> with the performance and efficiency they need at their scale.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Cross-validation Meta↔AWS</strong> importante: Meta — que tem <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MTIA\" title=\"_concepts/MTIA\">MTIA</a> + Broadcom custom + AMD chips + NVDA — escolheu <strong>Graviton para CPU-intensive agentic workloads</strong>. Implicação: ASIC vs GPU não é só &quot;Trainium vs NVDA AI accelerator&quot;, também é <strong>Graviton vs x86 (Intel/AMD)</strong> no layer de CPU.</p>\n<p>Graviton: <strong>40% better price-perf vs any other x86</strong>; <strong>98% of top 1000 EC2 customers</strong> usa.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Agentic AI thesis: GPU + CPU</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;AI is commonly seen as a GPU story, but the rise of agentic workloads, real-time reasoning, code generation, reinforcement learning, and multi-step task orchestration is driving <strong>massive CPU demand as well</strong>. As post-training and inference scale up, the compute required pulls heavily on CPUs.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Convergente com tese Fubon &quot;agentic AI requires CPU&quot; (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=TSM\" title=\"wiki/TSM\">TSM</a> — AMD em N2 driver). <strong>AMZN é beneficiário direto</strong> dessa convergência via Graviton.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 AWS AI = 260x larger em 3-yr mark vs original AWS</strong></h3>\n<ul><li>AWS AI revenue run rate <strong>&gt;$15B</strong> at 3-yr mark do current AI wave</li><li>AWS original 3 anos pós-launch: <strong>$58M run rate</strong></li><li><strong>AWS AI is 260x larger</strong> at the same 3-yr mark</li><li>Framing histórico: AWS está vivendo <strong>outro inflection scale-up</strong> (similar ao primeiro ciclo 2010-2015)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 NVIDIA partnership reaffirmed (não é replacement)</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;While the largest number of AI chips we&#x27;re bringing in are Trainium, we continue to have a <strong>deep partnership with NVIDIA</strong>. We have immense respect for them, continue to order substantial quantities, <strong>we&#x27;ll be partners as long as I can foresee</strong>, and we&#x27;ll always have customers who want to run NVIDIA on AWS.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Sinaliza: Trainium <strong>wins incremental workloads, não substitui NVDA</strong>. Coexistência multi-vendor é o steady-state.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 OpenAI models live em Bedrock + Stateful API thesis</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>GPT-5.4 live em Bedrock</strong> desde dia anterior à call; <strong>5.5 coming &quot;next couple of weeks&quot;</strong></li><li><strong>Bedrock Managed Agents</strong> (powered by OpenAI partnership) — Stateful Runtime Environment preview lançado dia anterior</li><li>Andy: <em>&quot;future of how these agents are going to be built. <strong>Something that nobody else has.</strong>&quot;</em></li><li>Codex e similar models também coming</li><li>Tese estratégica: <strong>AI workloads movem de stateless (&quot;tokens in/out&quot;) → stateful agents</strong> (store identity + state + conversations + tool reach)</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Memory shortage = tailwind escondido de cloud migration</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;Cost of these components, particularly memory, has <strong>skyrocketed</strong>. ... The interesting thing we see is that it is a <strong>further impetus pushing companies who have on-premises infrastructure into the cloud</strong>. Suppliers are prioritizing their very largest customers, <strong>which cloud providers are</strong>. We have a lot more supply than what others have.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Implicação cruzada: enquanto Meta/MSFT/AMZN/GOOGL estão pagando mais por componente (CapEx pressure), <strong>AWS está se beneficiando como destination da migração pelas enterprises</strong> que não conseguem allocation própria. Memory cycle vira <strong>dual headwind/tailwind</strong> (cost up, demand up).</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Backlog $364B (ex-Anthropic) + breadth across customers</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;The backlog for Q1 is <strong>$364 billion</strong>. That does not include the recent deal that we announced with Anthropic for over $100 billion. There&#x27;s reasonable breadth in that as well. <strong>It&#x27;s not just one customer or two customers</strong>.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Pro-forma backlog <strong>&gt;$465B</strong>. Inclui novos signed customers since last call: <strong>OpenAI, Anthropic, Meta, NVIDIA, Uber, U.S. Bank, Fox, Southwest Airlines, U.S. Army, Bloomberg, Cerebras, AT&amp;T, Nokia, Fundamental, National Geographic, PGA TOUR</strong>.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Apple direct-to-device deal via Leo + Globalstar acquisition planejado</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Apple agreement</strong> confirmed: Amazon Leo to power <strong>direct-to-device satellite services for iPhones and Apple Watches</strong></li><li><strong>Globalstar acquisition planejado</strong> — extends Leo&#x27;s network with direct-to-device + scarce global spectrum</li><li><strong>Delta Airlines: half fleet starting 2028</strong> committed</li><li>Outras revenue commitments: JetBlue, AT&amp;T, Vodafone, DIRECTV LatAm, Australia NBN, DP World Tour, NASA</li><li><strong>&gt;250 satélites em órbita</strong> (após latest launch)</li><li><strong>20+ launches este ano</strong>, <strong>30+ em 2027</strong></li><li><strong>Leo commercial service launches Q3 FY26</strong> (track), capitalizing certain costs Q4</li><li>Leo Q2 FY26 NA cost: <strong>+$1B YoY</strong> (manufacturing + launching satellites em prep service)</li></ul>\n<p>Andy: Leo &quot;has a chance to be a <strong>very large many billion dollar revenue business</strong> ... I like the <strong>free cash flow and ROIC characteristics</strong> of that business in the medium-long term.&quot; Compara explicitamente ao early AWS — &quot;characteristics reminiscent of AWS.&quot;</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Internal AI productivity validated — &quot;5 people, 65 days&quot;</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We swapped out the engine of the service while we were also running the service full tilt, and <strong>normally that would have taken 40 or 50 people about a year</strong> to do, and we took <strong>5 really smart people, AI-forward-thinking people building on agentic coding tools</strong>, and those 5 people <strong>rebuilt it in 65 days</strong>.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p>Productivity gain de <strong>40x</strong> em headcount-effort terms (50 people × 1 ano = 50 person-years vs 5 people × 2 meses = ~0.83 person-years = ~60x effort reduction; even more in calendar time = ~5.6x faster). <strong>Validação interna do thesis &quot;AI changes work&quot;</strong> que Susan Li (Meta) também referenciou.</p>\n<h3>Stores updates ainda relevantes</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Grocery $150B GSV em 2025 = 2nd largest grocer in US</strong></li><li>Whole Foods: 550 stores hoje, <strong>100 more coming</strong></li><li>Same-day perishables em <strong>2,300+ cities</strong>, perishable sales <strong>+40x YoY</strong></li><li><strong>Amazon Now (30-min delivery) em 9 countries</strong>, India +25% MoM</li><li>1- e 3-hour delivery em <strong>90,000+ items</strong></li><li><strong>Rufus</strong>: MAU <strong>+115% YoY</strong>, engagement <strong>+400% YoY</strong>, com auto-buy quando atinge preço-alvo</li><li><strong>Health AI</strong> launched (24/7 personal health agent backed by One Medical clinicians)</li><li><strong>Strands</strong>: 25M+ downloads (3x QoQ); <strong>AgentCore</strong>: 1 agent every 10 secs; <strong>Kiro</strong>: developers 2x QoQ; <strong>Transform</strong>: 1.56M+ hours saved; <strong>Quick</strong>: customers 4x QoQ + v1 desktop launched</li></ul>\n<h3>Ads updates Q1 FY26</h3>\n<ul><li>$17.2B (+22% YoY) já reportado no press release</li><li><strong>Netflix partnership &quot;deepened&quot;</strong>: Amazon Audiences = AMZN signals applied to Netflix viewers</li><li><strong>Comcast Advertising partnership</strong> (local ads)</li><li><strong>Interactive video ad capabilities</strong> com Samsung TVs</li><li><strong>Creative Agent expandida para 7 countries</strong></li><li><strong>Sponsored Brand Prompts em Rufus</strong>: ~20% engagement continuation rate</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>CapEx posture (vs Meta)</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;I don&#x27;t have a new update on capital. <strong>Our plan is largely the same</strong>, but we do view this as truly a <strong>once-in-a-lifetime opportunity</strong> where every application that we know of is going to be reinvented. ... I expect that we will invest a significant amount of capital over the coming years to pursue that opportunity.&quot;</em> — Andy Jassy</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Contraste explícito com Meta</strong> (que raised CapEx FY26 $115-135B → $125-145B no mesmo dia). AMZN: <strong>CapEx framework intacto</strong> — não há sinal de raise. Cash CapEx Q1 = <strong>$43.2B</strong> (transcript explicit). Press release reportava $44.2B (cash + finance leases).</p>\n<h3>Implicações cruzadas</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=META\" title=\"wiki/META\">META</a> — Graviton commitment &quot;tens of millions of cores&quot; é data point novo. Multi-vendor diversification confirmada <strong>também no CPU layer</strong> (não só accelerator).</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> — Trainium $225B commitments + 30% price-perf advantage <strong>não substituem NVDA</strong> mas confirmam loss of share <strong>incremental</strong>. NVDA = &quot;deep partnership for as long as I can foresee.&quot;</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — $50B standalone equiv + 30% perf advantage = data point estrutural na tese ASIC.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — backlog $364B ex-Anthropic + Trainium $225B = demand signals fortes; memory shortage = tailwind para hyperscalers vs on-prem.</li></ul></section>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/AMZN.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/AMZN.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
